Interested in participating in a clinical research study or know someone who
is?

   NIMH offers clinical trials for adults and children at the NIH Clinical
   Center in Bethesda, Maryland, and at many other locations across the
   United States.


Featured NIMH Trials

   NIMH studies currently recruiting participants; check periodically for
   new trial listings:

   Alzheimer's Disease and Related Disorders

   Anxiety Disorders
     * Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder
     * Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder
     * Co-Occurring Disorders

   Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD)

   Autism and Other Pervasive Developmental Disorders (PDDs)

   Mood Disorders
     * Bipolar Disorder
       (Manic-Depressive Illness)
     * Depression
     * Mood Disorders associated with
       the Menstrual Cycle, Pregnancy,
       and Menopause (Women)

   Schizophrenia and Related Disorders

   Sydenham Chorea

   Tourette Syndrome

Information Resources

   Clinical trials publications, news, information for healthy volunteers,
   and other clinical trials resources:

   Patients and Families
   Publications and other information about participating in clinical
   trials

   Researchers
   Research meetings, NCDEU, workshop summaries, articles, and news for
   investigators

   Healthy Volunteers
   Information on becoming a healthy volunteer for NIH clinical trials

   ClinicalTrials.gov
   The NIH/National Library of Medicine's registry of federally and
   privately funded clinical trials for all diseases

